<Base title="Fresh Pantry — Privacy Policy" doc>
  <nav><a href="/freshpantry/">← Fresh Pantry</a></nav>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="date">Effective July 7, 2026</p>

  <h2>The short version</h2>
  <p>Fresh Pantry stores your pantry data so your household can share it across devices.
     We keep only what the app needs to work, and none of it is sold, shared for advertising,
     or used to track you.</p>

  <h2>Your account</h2>
  <p>Syncing and household sharing require an account, created with your email address and a
     one-time code — no password, no profile beyond an optional display name. Without an
     account the app still works entirely on your device.</p>

  <h2>Your data</h2>
  <p>Your inventory, recipes, shopping lists, and meal plans are stored locally first, and
     synced to our servers so other members of your household and your other devices see the
     same pantry. They are visible only to you and the people you invite.</p>

  <h2>Paste import</h2>
  <p>When you paste text (like a receipt or a shopping list) to import it, that text is sent to
     our server, where an AI model turns it into suggested inventory updates for you to review.
     The pasted text is used only to produce those suggestions.</p>

  <h2>Stability and diagnostics</h2>
  <p>In release builds, Fresh Pantry uses Sentry — a third-party stability service — to help us
     find and fix problems. When something goes wrong, Sentry may receive:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Crash and hang reports</strong> — a technical stack trace, device model, and OS version.</li>
    <li><strong>Performance traces</strong> — timing of app operations, with no personal content.</li>
    <li><strong>Session replays</strong> — a recording of app screens from a small sample of sessions
        (and when errors occur). <strong>All text and all images are masked</strong>, so your pantry
        contents and pasted text are not visible in a replay.</li>
    <li><strong>Structured logs and metrics</strong> — anonymized counters and diagnostic logs.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Debug builds send nothing. This data is used only to improve stability — never for advertising
     or sold to anyone.</p>

  <h2>Deleting your data</h2>
  <p>Delete your account from Settings and your synced data is removed from our servers.</p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>If this policy ever changes, the update will be posted on this page with a new effective date.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions? Visit <a href="/freshpantry/support/">Support</a>.</p>
</Base>
